<item>
            <title>[LU-12217] ll_migrate() vs truncate deadlock</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12217</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;    ll_migrate() takes inode_lock and sends OST_GETATTR&lt;br/&gt;
    via ll_data_version(). The server sends BL AST to&lt;br/&gt;
    a truncate on the same client to release osc lock&lt;br/&gt;
    but it waits for the inode lock.&lt;br/&gt;
    It&apos;s a wrong locking order beacause all osc operations&lt;br/&gt;
    take ldlm locks before inode_lock.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    inode_lock was added to protect from simultaneous migrates&lt;br/&gt;
    from 1 client. But lli_lsm_sem is taken for parent,&lt;br/&gt;
    so inode_lock isn&apos;t needed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
